{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":650,"text":"I have a friend in Portugal"},{"time":2898,"text":"whose grandfather built a vehicle out of a bicycle"},{"time":5322,"text":"and a washing machine so he could transport his family."},{"time":8474,"text":"He did it because he couldn't afford a car,"},{"time":11018,"text":"but also because he knew how to build one."},{"time":13922,"text":"There was a time when we understood how things worked"},{"time":17058,"text":"and how they were made, so we could build and repair them,"},{"time":20890,"text":"or at the very least"},{"time":22017,"text":"make informed decisions about what to buy."},{"time":25497,"text":"Many of these do-it-yourself practices"},{"time":27889,"text":"were lost in the second half of the 20th century."},{"time":31098,"text":"But now, the maker community and the open-source model"},{"time":34770,"text":"are bringing this kind of knowledge about how things work"},{"time":37918,"text":"and what they're made of back into our lives,"},{"time":41113,"text":"and I believe we need to take them to the next level,"},{"time":44137,"text":"to the components things are made of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47105,"text":"For the most part, we still know"},{"time":49257,"text":"what traditional materials like paper and textiles are made of"},{"time":52779,"text":"and how they are produced."},{"time":54808,"text":"But now we have these amazing, futuristic composites --"},{"time":58871,"text":"plastics that change shape,"},{"time":61074,"text":"paints that conduct electricity,"},{"time":63426,"text":"pigments that change color, fabrics that light up."},{"time":67842,"text":"Let me show you some examples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74169,"text":"So conductive ink allows us to paint circuits"},{"time":77885,"text":"instead of using the traditional"},{"time":79828,"text":"printed circuit boards or wires."},{"time":82426,"text":"In the case of this little example I'm holding,"},{"time":84815,"text":"we used it to create a touch sensor that reacts to my skin"},{"time":88696,"text":"by turning on this little light."},{"time":91411,"text":"Conductive ink has been used by artists,"},{"time":94506,"text":"but recent developments indicate that we will soon be able"},{"time":97881,"text":"to use it in laser printers and pens."},{"time":102376,"text":"And this is a sheet of acrylic infused"},{"time":104706,"text":"with colorless light-diffusing particles."},{"time":107502,"text":"What this means is that, while regular acrylic"},{"time":110119,"text":"only diffuses light around the edges,"},{"time":112467,"text":"this one illuminates across the entire surface"},{"time":115737,"text":"when I turn on the lights around it."},{"time":118650,"text":"Two of the known applications for this material"},{"time":120952,"text":"include interior design and multi-touch systems."},{"time":126065,"text":"And thermochromic pigments"},{"time":128066,"text":"change color at a given temperature."},{"time":130679,"text":"So I'm going to place this on a hot plate"},{"time":133465,"text":"that is set to a temperature only slightly higher than ambient"},{"time":136970,"text":"and you can see what happens."},{"time":142816,"text":"So one of the principle applications for this material"},{"time":145576,"text":"is, amongst other things, in baby bottles,"},{"time":148818,"text":"so it indicates when the contents are cool enough to drink."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154172,"text":"So these are just a few of what are commonly known"},{"time":156928,"text":"as smart materials."},{"time":158837,"text":"In a few years, they will be in many of the objects"},{"time":161777,"text":"and technologies we use on a daily basis."},{"time":165136,"text":"We may not yet have the flying cars science fiction promised us,"},{"time":169350,"text":"but we can have walls that change color"},{"time":171719,"text":"depending on temperature,"},{"time":173481,"text":"keyboards that roll up,"},{"time":175375,"text":"and windows that become opaque at the flick of a switch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179807,"text":"So I'm a social scientist by training,"},{"time":182312,"text":"so why am I here today talking about smart materials?"},{"time":186169,"text":"Well first of all, because I am a maker."},{"time":188882,"text":"I'm curious about how things work"},{"time":191288,"text":"and how they are made,"},{"time":192915,"text":"but also because I believe we should have a deeper understanding"},{"time":196223,"text":"of the components that make up our world,"},{"time":199044,"text":"and right now, we don't know enough about"},{"time":201524,"text":"these high-tech composites our future will be made of."},{"time":205213,"text":"Smart materials are hard to obtain in small quantities."},{"time":208738,"text":"There's barely any information available on how to use them,"},{"time":212778,"text":"and very little is said about how they are produced."},{"time":216675,"text":"So for now, they exist mostly in this realm"},{"time":219342,"text":"of trade secrets and patents"},{"time":222054,"text":"only universities and corporations have access to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226166,"text":"So a little over three years ago, Kirsty Boyle and I"},{"time":229015,"text":"started a project we called Open Materials."},{"time":232232,"text":"It's a website where we,"},{"time":234039,"text":"and anyone else who wants to join us,"},{"time":236551,"text":"share experiments, publish information,"},{"time":239607,"text":"encourage others to contribute whenever they can,"},{"time":242807,"text":"and aggregate resources such as research papers"},{"time":246816,"text":"and tutorials by other makers like ourselves."},{"time":250156,"text":"We would like it to become a large,"},{"time":252778,"text":"collectively generated database"},{"time":255316,"text":"of do-it-yourself information on smart materials."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259609,"text":"But why should we care"},{"time":261829,"text":"how smart materials work and what they are made of?"},{"time":265592,"text":"First of all, because we can't shape what we don't understand,"},{"time":269770,"text":"and what we don't understand and use"},{"time":272122,"text":"ends up shaping us."},{"time":274330,"text":"The objects we use, the clothes we wear,"},{"time":277082,"text":"the houses we live in, all have a profound impact"},{"time":280646,"text":"on our behavior, health and quality of life."},{"time":284229,"text":"So if we are to live in a world made of smart materials,"},{"time":287370,"text":"we should know and understand them."},{"time":290729,"text":"Secondly, and just as important,"},{"time":293073,"text":"innovation has always been fueled by tinkerers."},{"time":296433,"text":"So many times, amateurs, not experts,"},{"time":299818,"text":"have been the inventors and improvers"},{"time":302137,"text":"of things ranging from mountain bikes"},{"time":304617,"text":"to semiconductors, personal computers,"},{"time":307929,"text":"airplanes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310868,"text":"The biggest challenge is that material science is complex"},{"time":314897,"text":"and requires expensive equipment."},{"time":317393,"text":"But that's not always the case."},{"time":319561,"text":"Two scientists at University of Illinois understood this"},{"time":323149,"text":"when they published a paper on a simpler method"},{"time":325749,"text":"for making conductive ink."},{"time":328169,"text":"Jordan Bunker, who had had"},{"time":330081,"text":"no experience with chemistry until then,"},{"time":333041,"text":"read this paper and reproduced the experiment"},{"time":335828,"text":"at his maker space using only off-the-shelf substances"},{"time":340217,"text":"and tools."},{"time":341809,"text":"He used a toaster oven,"},{"time":343410,"text":"and he even made his own vortex mixer,"},{"time":346376,"text":"based on a tutorial by another scientist/maker."},{"time":350411,"text":"Jordan then published his results online,"},{"time":353163,"text":"including all the things he had tried and didn't work,"},{"time":356651,"text":"so others could study and reproduce it."},{"time":359795,"text":"So Jordan's main form of innovation"},{"time":362467,"text":"was to take an experiment created in a well-equipped lab"},{"time":366346,"text":"at the university"},{"time":367848,"text":"and recreate it in a garage in Chicago"},{"time":371035,"text":"using only cheap materials and tools he made himself."},{"time":375296,"text":"And now that he published this work,"},{"time":377569,"text":"others can pick up where he left"},{"time":379293,"text":"and devise even simpler processes and improvements."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383837,"text":"Another example I'd like to mention"},{"time":386053,"text":"is Hannah Perner-Wilson's Kit-of-No-Parts."},{"time":389718,"text":"Her project's goal is to highlight"},{"time":392598,"text":"the expressive qualities of materials"},{"time":395070,"text":"while focusing on the creativity and skills of the builder."},{"time":400094,"text":"Electronics kits are very powerful"},{"time":402534,"text":"in that they teach us how things work,"},{"time":405086,"text":"but the constraints inherent in their design"},{"time":408062,"text":"influence the way we learn."},{"time":410222,"text":"So Hannah's approach, on the other hand,"},{"time":412710,"text":"is to formulate a series of techniques"},{"time":415926,"text":"for creating unusual objects"},{"time":418625,"text":"that free us from pre-designed constraints"},{"time":421430,"text":"by teaching us about the materials themselves."},{"time":424841,"text":"So amongst Hannah's many impressive experiments,"},{"time":427574,"text":"this is one of my favorites."},{"time":429544,"text":"[\"Paper speakers\"]"},{"time":432961,"text":"What we're seeing here is just a piece of paper"},{"time":436239,"text":"with some copper tape on it connected to an mp3 player"},{"time":440681,"text":"and a magnet."},{"time":442334,"text":"(Music: \"Happy Together\")"},{"time":452931,"text":"So based on the research by Marcelo Coelho from MIT,"},{"time":456767,"text":"Hannah created a series of paper speakers"},{"time":459550,"text":"out of a wide range of materials"},{"time":461953,"text":"from simple copper tape to conductive fabric and ink."},{"time":466228,"text":"Just like Jordan and so many other makers,"},{"time":468964,"text":"Hannah published her recipes"},{"time":470591,"text":"and allows anyone to copy and reproduce them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475725,"text":"But paper electronics is one of the most promising branches"},{"time":478929,"text":"of material science"},{"time":480736,"text":"in that it allows us to create cheaper and flexible electronics."},{"time":484938,"text":"So Hannah's artisanal work,"},{"time":487494,"text":"and the fact that she shared her findings,"},{"time":489742,"text":"opens the doors to a series of new possibilities"},{"time":493562,"text":"that are both aesthetically appealing and innovative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499002,"text":"So the interesting thing about makers"},{"time":501907,"text":"is that we create out of passion and curiosity,"},{"time":504950,"text":"and we are not afraid to fail."},{"time":507029,"text":"We often tackle problems from unconventional angles,"},{"time":510917,"text":"and, in the process, end up discovering alternatives"},{"time":513906,"text":"or even better ways to do things."},{"time":516338,"text":"So the more people experiment with materials,"},{"time":520106,"text":"the more researchers are willing to share their research,"},{"time":523582,"text":"and manufacturers their knowledge,"},{"time":526022,"text":"the better chances we have to create technologies"},{"time":528862,"text":"that truly serve us all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":531800,"text":"So I feel a bit as Ted Nelson must have"},{"time":534293,"text":"when, in the early 1970s, he wrote,"},{"time":538004,"text":"\"You must understand computers now.\""},{"time":541002,"text":"Back then, computers were these large mainframes"},{"time":544856,"text":"only scientists cared about,"},{"time":546986,"text":"and no one dreamed of even having one at home."},{"time":549706,"text":"So it's a little strange that I'm standing here and saying,"},{"time":552682,"text":"\"You must understand smart materials now.\""},{"time":555722,"text":"Just keep in mind that acquiring preemptive knowledge"},{"time":559458,"text":"about emerging technologies"},{"time":561722,"text":"is the best way to ensure that we have a say"},{"time":564119,"text":"in the making of our future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":566282,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568753,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}